Tula SVT-40, Samozaryadnaya Vintovka Tokareva, Obrazets 1940 goda ("Tokarev Self-loading Rifle, Model of 1940").

 This rifle has the characteristic refurb plum bolt, comes with one ten-round detachable box magazine, and a cleaning rod.

 Designed basically by Fedor Tokarev in 1938, and refined in 1940, The SVT40 rifle cycles by means of a gas-operated short-stroke spring-loaded piston, with a tilting bolt. This weapon has a MUZZLE BRAKE, NOT a flash supressor/hider, and is legal to own and transfer in California. 

  The Izhevsk "arrow in a triangle" and "1940 stamp on the receiver identifies the arsenal and date of manafacture. The original arctic birch stock shows a bit of wear, but has no cracks or repairs. Serial # xx102x is stamped on the stock, receiver, and triggerguard as well as Â electropenciled on the plum colored bolt. The electropencil numbers and plum-colored bolt are signs of an arsenal rework, which is common with SVTs that went through this rebuild process. Like many SVTs, the receiver has the milled grooves for a scope mount, but no top notch to lock the scope mount in place.

  The barrel has the later 4 slot muzzle brake.Â  Standard 100-1500 meter sights. The rifle and stock are in very nice condition overall.
